  A  related  a  or  salt  must  stick  place  to  physical Q  The answer must be a situation when people think too quickly and make a decision without considering. Jump to conclusions is a common phrase when people think too quickly. Hurry home is a common phrase when people are in a hurry, but not necessarily because they are thinking too quickly. Building trust is a process that requires time, not a quick decision. Pay bills is a financial activity that is not related to thinking too quickly. Sing is a common activity when people are not thinking, but not a direct result of thinking too quickly. So the answer is jump to conclusions (a).

